==================
Sequence Tagger
- joshua, 13514012
==================

1. make sure you have all dependencies installed and able to run

     nltk
     numpy as np
     random
     pickle
     csv
     json
     pickle
     datetime
     tensorflow
     keras
     keras_contrib -> https://github.com/keras-team/keras-contrib
     sklearn

     * also download the word level embedding (polyglot) here: http://bit.ly/19bSjgz

2. import the library

     from Main import SeqTagger

3. create seqtagger object

	tagger = SeqTagger()

4. set parameters (optional, if not set the object will use default value)

	ex:
	 tagger.padsize = 100
	 tagger.char_padsize = 30
	 tagger.EMBEDDING_DIM = 50
	 tagger.CHAR_EMBEDDING_DIM = 50
	 tagger.optimizer = 'categorical_crossentropy'
	 tagger.patience = 4
	to view all configurable parameter, check "Data and other attributes" section in help(SeqTagger)

5. create seqtagger model

     SeqTagger(training data, development/validation data, testing data, pre-trained word embedding, pre-trained char embedding)

    ex:
     tagger.createModel('id-ud-train.pos', 'id-ud-dev.pos', 'id-ud-test.pos', 'polyglot.vec', 'polyglot-char.vec')

     tagger.createModel('train.txt', 'valid.txt', 'test.txt', 'polyglot.vec', 'polyglot-char.vec')


6. train the model

     tagger.trainFit()

7. evaluate the result

     tagger.evaluate()

8. save model

	 tagger.saveModel('savedmodelname')

9. load model

	 tagger.loadModel('savedmodelname')
	*to load model, you need to create the model first (createModel()) and set the embedding and training data that will be used
